## Summary
Survey map lacks obvious zoom controls; relies on keyboard/mouse/touch. Low-res images aren’t handled (no upscaling guidance), and supported image formats aren’t communicated.

## Impact
- Hard to navigate maps without visible zoom in/out controls.
- Low-res imports stay blurry with no guidance on recommended resolution; unclear whether upscaling is applied or advisable.
- Users don’t know which image types are supported or preferred.

## Expected
- Add visible zoom controls (buttons/slider) for map navigation alongside existing input methods.
- Provide guidance on resolution; consider optional upscaling for non-scale-critical images (and warn against it for drawn-to-scale plans).
- Document supported image formats and pros/cons in the UI (PNG/JPG/SVG/etc.).

## Location
- Survey map view/import UX
